# Authentication Patterns

## NextAuth v5 Configuration

Configuration in `src/auth.config.ts`:

```typescript
// ✅ GOOD - Session callback enrichment
callbacks: {
  async session({ session, token }) {
    if (token.sub) {
      // Fetch fresh user data from DB
      const user = await db.query.users.findFirst({
        where: eq(users.id, token.sub),
      });
      
      if (user) {
        session.user = {
          id: user.id,
          name: user.name,
          email: user.email,
          // ... other fields
        };
      }
    }
    return session;
  },
}
```

## Password Handling

```typescript
// ✅ GOOD - Hash with bcryptjs (10 rounds)
import bcrypt from "bcryptjs";

const hashedPassword = await bcrypt.hash(password, 10);
const isValid = await bcrypt.compare(password, hashedPassword);
```

## Session Access

```typescript
// ✅ GOOD - Server components/actions
import { auth } from "@/auth.config";
const session = await auth();

// ✅ GOOD - Client components
"use client";
import { useSession } from "next-auth/react";
const { data: session } = useSession();
```

## Type Augmentation

Extend session types in `@types/next-auth.d.ts`:

```typescript
declare module "next-auth" {
  interface Session {
    user: {
      id: string;
      name: string;
      email: string;
      phone?: string;
      balance?: number;
    };
  }
}
```

## Route Protection
- Dashboard layout checks session
- Redirects to `/login` if missing
- Auth pages redirect to `/dashboard` if authenticated
